He returned to New York in 1937, working with Mezz Mezzrow and Sidney Bechet.: 99 In 1943, he moved to Los Angeles, where he led his own band, played for motion pictures, and appeared on the radio program The Orson Welles Almanac (1944).

sentences: Arthur James "Zutty" Singleton (May 14, 1898 – July 14, 1975) was an American jazz drummer.
In Chicago, Singleton played with Doc Cook, Dave Peyton, Jimmie Noone, and theater bands, then joined Louis Armstrong's band with Earl Hines.
